            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <lev1>
                    <title>NEW DESIGNED WATER PUMP ASSEMBLY</title>
                    <para>A new water pump assembly designed to accommodate
                        <emph type="bold">"SPIN-ON"</emph>
                        type fan drive clutches is released replacing water pump assembly designed to accommodate
                        <emph type="bold">"STUD MOUNT"</emph>type fan drive clutches for all DT/DTA-360 and DT/DTA-466
                        diesel engines.
                    </para>
                    <specpara>
                        <note>
                            <para>Water pump assemblies for either "SPIN-ON" type or "STUD MOUNT" type fan drive
                                clutches are NOT interchangeable. The component parts of both assemblies are identical
                                except for the pump shaft, pulley hub and hub nut. Refer to
                                <hotlnk xrefid="f9212131">Figure 1</hotlnk>.
                            </para>
                        </note>
                    </specpara>
                    <figure id="f9212131" figsize="pg-wide">
                        <graphic filename="../tsifigures/g9212131.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 1. Water Pump Assemblies Comparison</caption>
                    </figure>
                    <lev2>
                        <title>Water Pump Shafts</title>
                        <para>Refer to
                            <hotlnk xrefid="f9212132">Figure 2</hotlnk>.
                        </para>
                        <figure id="f9212132" figsize="pg-wide">
                            <graphic filename="../tsifigures/g9212132.webp" type="webp"/>
                            <caption>Figure 2. Water Pump Shaft Comparison</caption>
                        </figure>
                    </lev2>
                    <lev2>
                        <title>Pulley Hub</title>
                        <para>Refer to
                            <hotlnk xrefid="f9212133">Figure 3</hotlnk>.
                        </para>
                        <para>The thickness of new designed water pump pulley hub is reduced to .975 inches compared to
                            old water pump pulley hub thickness of 1.500 inches.
                        </para>
                        <para>This reduction in thickness allows a greater mounting surface for the "SPIN-ON" fan drive
                            clutch.
                        </para>
                        <figure id="f9212133" figsize="pg-wide">
                            <graphic filename="../tsifigures/g9212133.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                            <caption>Figure 3. Pulley Hub Comparison</caption>
                        </figure>
                    </lev2>
                    <lev2>
                        <title>Hub Nut</title>
                        <para>Refer to
                            <hotlnk xrefid="f9212134">Figure 4</hotlnk>.
                        </para>
                        <para>A 3/4-16 inch UNF LEFT HAND THREAD hex lock nut is released for new designed water pump
                            assembly to accommodate new water pump shaft equipped with LEFT HAND THREADS. The old water
                            pump assembly is equipped with a lock nut that does
                            <emph type="bold">NOT</emph>
                            have LEFT HAND THREADS, refer to NOTE below.
                        </para>
                        <specpara>
                            <note>
                                <para>When hub hex lock nut is ordered for service on old water pump assembly, a flange
                                    lock nut having the same part number will be furnished. Refer to
                                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9212134">Figure 4.</hotlnk>
                                </para>
                            </note>
                        </specpara>
                        <figure id="f9212134" figsize="pg-wide">
                            <graphic filename="../tsifigures/g9212134.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                            <caption>Figure 4. Hub Nut Comparison</caption>
                        </figure>
