                <lev1>
                    <title>NEW FAN DRIVES</title>
                    <para>New fan drives are released to accommodate "SPIN-ON" type fan drive clutches for DT/DTA-360
                        and DT/DTA-466 diesel engines.
                    </para>
                    <para>The fan pulley, water pump pulley and air compressor drive pulley (3900FC and 3800
                        applications only) for "SPIN-ON" type fan drive clutches are as follows:
                    </para>
                    <lev2>
                        <title>Fan Pulley</title>
                        <para>Fan pulley is unchanged and remains for both "SPIN-ON" or "STUD MOUNT" type fan drive
                            clutches.
                        </para>
                    </lev2>
                    <lev2>
                        <title>Water Pump Pulley</title>
                        <para>A two-groove water pump pulley with twelve mounting holes, drive pulley spacer and fan
                            pulley spacer and six (6) 3/8 inch studs will continue to be used with the "STUD MOUNT" type
                            fan drive clutches.
                        </para>
                    </lev2>
                    <lev2>
                        <title>Air Compressor Drive Pulley</title>
                        <para>Refer to
                            <hotlnk xrefid="f9212135">Figure 5</hotlnk>.
                        </para>
                        <figure id="f9212135" figsize="pg-wide">
                            <graphic filename="../tsifigures/g9212135.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                            <caption>Figure 5. Air Compressor Drive Pulley Comparison (DT/DTA-360 3900FC And 3800
                                Applications And DT-466 3900FC Application Only)
                            </caption>
                        </figure>
                        <para>(DT/DTA-360 3900FC and 3800 Bus Applications Only and DT-466 3900FC Bus Applications
                            Only
                        </para>
                        <para>A new sheet metal, single groove, air compressor drive pulley with six mounting holes and
                            without spacers, is released to accommodate the new "SPIN-ON" type fan drive clutches.
                        </para>
                    </lev2>
                    <lev2>
                        <title>Water Pump and Fan Pulley</title>
                        <para>Refer to
                            <hotlnk xrefid="f9212136">Figure 6</hotlnk>.
                        </para>
                        <para>For all applications EXCEPT DT/DTA-360 3900FC or 3800 Buses and DT-466 3900FC Bus.</para>
                        <figure id="f9212136" figsize="pg-wide">
                            <graphic filename="../tsifigures/g9212136.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                            <caption>Figure 6. Water Pump And Fan Pulley Comparison (For All Applications Except
                                DT/DTA-360 3900FC and 3800 Buses and DT-466 3900FC Bus)
                            </caption>
                        </figure>
                        <para>To accommodate new "SPIN-ON" type fan drive clutches, water pump and fan pulley (for all
                            applications except DT/DTA-360 FC or 3800 Buses and DT-466 FC Bus) are modified as follows:
                        </para>
                        <seqlist>
                            <item>
                                <para>A new two-groove water pump and fan pulley with six mounting holes, together with
                                    six (6) 3/8-16 x 1 inch hex-hd capscrews and six (6) 3/8 inch hardened washers are
                                    available for "SPIN-ON" type fan drive clutches.
                                </para>
                                <para>Two-groove water pump and fan pulley with twelve mounting holes are being retained
                                    for service on "STUD MOUNT" type fan drive clutches.
                                </para>
                            </item>
                            <item>
                                <para>The water pump pulley is unchanged and remains for both "SPIN-ON" or "STUD MOUNT"
                                    type fan drive clutches.
                                </para>
                            </item>
                            <item>
                                <para>The fan pulley spacer together with mounting hardware and six (6) studs will only
                                    be serviced for "STUD MOUNT" type fan drive clutches.
                                </para>
                            </item>
                        </seqlist>
                    </lev2>
                </lev1>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
